This paper is about reinforcement learning algorithms, specifically target-based temporal difference learning algorithms. The paper provides theoretical analysis on their convergence and compares them to standard TD-learning. This work is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), control systems (cs.SY), neural networks (cs.NE), and data structures (cs.DS).
